QUESTION:
Input: root = [10,5,-3,3,2,null,11,3,-2,null,1], targetSum = 8
Output: 3
Explanation: The paths that sum to 8 are shown.


SOLUTION
(Maybe not the best way out there )
TIME COMPLEXITY:O(n)
SPACE COMPLEXITY:O(n)


CODE:
Since you have solved Path sum 1&2 
Its the same , just that I create a dfs of each node and go through it.

/**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * public class TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode left;
 *     TreeNode right;
 *     TreeNode() {}
 *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }
 *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {
 *         this.val = val;
 *         this.left = left;
 *         this.right = right;
 *     }
 * }
 */
class Solution {
    int count=0;
    public int pathSum(TreeNode root, int targetSum) {
        dfs(root,targetSum);
        return count;
    }
    public void dfs(TreeNode root,int targetSum){
        if(root==null)return;
        findpaths(root,targetSum,0,new ArrayList<>());
        dfs(root.left,targetSum);
        dfs(root.right,targetSum);
    }
    public void findpaths(TreeNode root,int targetSum,long sum,ArrayList<Integer>list){
        if(root==null)return;
        sum+=root.val;
        list.add(root.val);
        if(sum==targetSum){
            count++;
        }
        findpaths(root.left,targetSum,sum,list);
        findpaths(root.right,targetSum,sum,list);
    }
}
